org.overture.core.tests

Class ParseTcFacade

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.overture.core.tests.ParseTcFacade

  • public abstract class ParseTcFacade
extends Object
    Parse and Type Check VDM Sources. This class is the main interaction point with the Overture parser and type checker. It calls on them to process and construct ASTs from various kinds of sources.

    All methods in this class will cause test failures if they cannot process the source. If you need more fine-grained control over the parsing and type checking processes, we suggest using ParserUtil and TypeCheckerUtil .
    Author:
    ldc

                                            String testName,
                                            Dialect dialect)
                                     throws ParserException,

        Parse and type check a VDM model. This method will try to check the model in VDM classic and VDM 10. It assumes the model sources are encoded in UTF-8.
        Parameters:
        sources - the List of File containing the model's sources
        testName - the name of the test calling this method (used for failure reporting)
        dialect - the VDM Dialect the source is written in
        Returns:
        the AST of the model, as a list of INode
        Throws:
        LexException
